This paper is about accelerating deep learning frameworks, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories in computer science. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper focuses on improving the performance of deep learning models. The second likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision), as the paper mentions specific models like AlexNet and ResNet-18 that are commonly used in computer vision tasks. The third likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as the paper deals with optimizing the performance of neural networks. The fourth likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), as the paper discusses using GPUs to accelerate deep learning. The fifth likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as deep learning is a subfield of AI.
